Because growth is almost an imperative in today's business, it is crucial to understand the strategic fundamentals underpinning profitable growth. The course connects frameworks from economics, strategy and management to the practical experiences of firms to illustrate why some businesses can grow successfully while others struggle. The cases and examples in this course will focus on middle-market (not start-ups) and industry leaders in search of expanding their business. The course starts with firm life-cycle theory and the meaning of growth. Growth through scaling, growth through entry (incl. internationalization), and growth through partnerships and acquisition is focused at. Each strategy has its pitfalls and handling those will be addressed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with knowledge and skills to understand why some ventures grow and how growth can be achieved. It focuses on the different forms and process of growth and how to manage it. The course aims at providing students with a thorough grounding in theories related to the growth process and models. The course additionally gives knowledge on theory and models concerning analysis and solving the problems of growth.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the student should:  * know the characteristics of growing and non-growing firms;  * be able to critically analyse complex situations regarding growth during an organization's development in a changing environment;  * be able to evaluate the need of strategic resources and capabilities for growth;  * have overeview of different growth strategies and can critically evaluate their appropriateness in the context of a given venture;  * be able to analyse and predict the tensions caused by growth;  * be able to analyse, evaluate and recommend specific actions organizations can take to grow their value and avoid common growth pitfalls.
